  "risk_analysis": "By moving the battery degradation closer to the 50% threshold and introducing persistent shutdowns that continue after recent software updates, along with intermittent unresponsiveness and inconclusive diagnostics, the claim edges closer to qualifying as a defect under Section 3.1. However, the lack of definitive evidence of a manufacturing defect and the role of normal aging/software factors creates a borderline scenario requiring nuanced judgment."
}

