{
  "title": "Third ADH Claim Filed with Conflicting Signs of Sudden Liquid Ingress and Possible Prolonged Exposure",
  "description": "Customer files a third ADH claim within the Plan Term following two prior ADH claims serviced under AppleCare+. The new incident involves irregular touch responsiveness combined with localized corrosion on one internal component, linked to exposure to heavy mist in a poorly ventilated indoor environment over several hours. The customer states this was unintentional and unexpected, noting the iPhone was enclosed in a water-resistant case that was possibly compromised but without visible damage. Apple's diagnostics indicate moisture presence primarily inside near the corrosion site, along with subtle mechanical stress markers, but do not clearly confirm if the damage resulted from a sudden accidental external event or gradual environmental degradation. This ambiguity complicates determining if the damage qualifies as accidental damage from handling or disallowed environmental wear.",
  "adjustments": "Changed the environmental exposure from a brief outdoor rain shower to prolonged heavy mist exposure indoors in poor ventilation, implying possible gradual effect. Added evidence of localized corrosion rather than subtle internal anomalies. Introduced possible case compromise without visible damage, increasing uncertainty about accidental versus gradual cause.",
  "risk_analysis": "The shift to prolonged, indoor heavy mist exposure erodes the certainty that the damage stems from a clearly identifiable, sudden accidental event. The presence of corrosion suggests environmental wear that typically falls outside ADH coverage. However, the alleged unintentional nature and potential minor case compromise introduce doubt. Mixed diagnostic signals and the third claim status push the scenario nearer to the threshold between valid ADH coverage and exclusion based on policy limits and damage definitions."
}

